text.section:
The Board may reinstate the license of a former licensee who has failed to renew the license for any reason if the former licensee:
Meets the continuing education requirements of § 1A-306 of this subtitle for each year that the license has lapsed;
Applies for reinstatement more than 30 days after the license renewal deadline;
Submits to the Board an application for reinstatement on the form required by the Board; and
Pays to the Board a reinstatement fee and a renewal fee set by the Board.
